comment: Pachulia (MIL) sets a back screen on Watson (IND) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
West (IND) sets a screen on Carter-Williams (MIL) and gives him an opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Miles (IND) sets a screen on Middleton (MIL) under the rim and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
West (IND) runs into Ilyasova (MIL) after he receives the pass, affecting his RSBQ.
Ilyasova (MIL) dislodges Scola (IND) with his forearm as they attempt to rebound.
Stuckey (IND) remains legal while following the path of Middleton (MIL), not affecting his RSBQ on the drive. Stuckey takes several steps back when contact is made.
Contact between Scola (IND) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) occurs after the game clock has expired.

After communicating with the Replay Center, officials determined that the foul by Mahinmi (IND) met the criteria for a Flagrant Foul Type 1. All Flagrant Fouls are reviewed by Rod Thorn and subject to up/downgrade, as appropriate.

After communicating with the Replay Center, officials determined that the foul by Mahinmi (IND) met the criteria for a Flagrant Foul Type 1. All Flagrant Fouls are reviewed by Rod Thorn and subject to up/downgrade, as appropriate.

LATR shows Pachulia (MIL) hit the ball during rebound attempt. LHH shows Stuckey (IND) attempt to reach the ball, but appears to get to it only after it has hit the line. Poss. correctly given to IND. (Play not reviewable unless last 2-mins of OT.)
Middleton (MIL) dislodges Stuckey (IND) under the rim.
Scola (IND) and Middleton (MIL) lock up and then release.
RHH and R-Slash show Antetokounmpo (MIL) make contact with Hill's (IND) face as he attempts to get to the ball.
Pachulia (MIL) establishes his pivot foot after catching the pass in the paint and releases his pass before lifting it from the floor.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) receives the pass, establishing left foot as pivot, and then moves the pivot foot before releasing the ball.
Contact between Middleton (MIL) and Hill (IND) is incidental to their attempt to rebound.

Scola (IND) beats Carter-Williams (MIL) to the spot (expected point of contact), and then moves backward to defend (which is legal). He makes "high-five" contact with Carter-Williams' hand after he releases, which is also legal.
RHH shows Pachulia's (MIL) contact with Hill (IND) is incidental to his attempt to get the rebound.
RATR shows Stuckey (IND) does not extend his arm when contact is made with Middleton (MIL).
RHH shows Pachulia (MIL) step in front of Stuckey (IND) sideways on his drive without giving him an opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Hill (IND) maintains legal guarding position as he defends the drive to the basket by Carter-Williams (MIL).
Ilyasova (MIL) beats Hill (IND) to the point of contact, giving him an opportunity to stop and/or change direct.
Stuckey (IND) continues along Middleton's (MIL) path as he defends him without affecting his RSBQ.
Carter-Williams (MIL) fouls Hill (IND) as inbound is released.
Pachulia (MIL) sets a screen on Hill (IND) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
